        <abstract> 
<p>Discusses A. C. Ramsay’s article ["On the denudation of South Wales", <hi rend="italic">Mem. Geol. Surv. G. B.</hi> 1 (1846)]. Mentions his own paper ["Volcanic phenomena in South America", <hi rend="italic">Collected papers</hi> 1: 53–86]. Emphasises that sedimentary deposits are not ordinarily preserved.</p> 
        </abstract>
